    <div class="text">
      <p>1970s horror meets 2020 feminist activism as Dr Carnesky’s Incredible Bleeding Woman paints the country red…</p>

      <p>Putting the magic back into menstruation, show woman and artist Marisa Carnesky reinvents menstrual rituals for a new era, drawing on the hidden power of a forgotten matriarchal past. Referencing representations of women and blood from ancient mythology to classic horror movies, menstruation takes centre stage in a profound exploration of what it means to be ‘female’. Issues around fertility, body shame, taboo and lost ancient herstories are scrutinised, politicised & reclaimed.</p>
