      <p>Maayan Sophia Weisstub showcases a new way of looking at the menstrual cycle, an integral part of the female experience. Shedding light on what is so often hidden, she creates a connection between the repressed and forbidden pubic blood to positive, sensual experiences; a glass of wine, a sought-after red carpet event. </p>

      <p>Thus the outcast becomes a visible and positive experience, something one doesn't need to be ashamed of – something to accept with love. </p>
