      <p>Polish photographer Angelika Marciszewska dedicates her works to body positivity in relation to the female body. This image is from the #krwawie (bleed) series which was created for the initiative Akcja Menstruacja (Menstruation Action), the first foundation in Poland to combat menstrual poverty and actively dismantles the period taboo. Her raw images destigmatize and call for self-love, in which body shapes and sizes are represented in the context of the period, far from the heteronormative view.</p>
